# Pre-push typecheck
#
# Runs the same strict tsc pass Vercel's production build does, so we
# catch Next.js-only type errors (FC type narrowing, server-component
# prop shapes, route-handler signatures, ReactElement<DocumentProps>
# mismatches) before they hit the remote.
#
# Three out of three deploy failures since adding this session's work
# were exactly this class of error — Vitest's transform is looser than
# Next's production tsc on API route handlers and server pages, so a
# fully green `npm test` does not guarantee a successful build.
#
# Takes ~60–90s on a dev machine with enough RAM. If the project has
# grown past what tsc can handle in a single pass, run `npm run build`
# locally instead — that's the authoritative check and mirrors Vercel
# exactly.
#
# To bypass in an emergency use:
#   git push --no-verify
# …but prefer fixing the error.

npm run typecheck
